Characterization of thus obtained black residue revealed some interesting aspects. The TEM and atomic composition data (Fig. 4
                           ) shows the sheet like structures with iron doping. The XRD peak of the residue (Fig. 5
                           ) is located at a relatively higher 2θ of 26.59 in comparison to 24.6 of K-doped GO, which further supports the doping of iron into GO sheets of the residue (Singh et al., 2013; Pradhan et al., 2021).
